---
import DocsLayout from "@/layouts/DocsLayout.astro"
---

<DocsLayout title="Custom events — Kobbe" description="Track custom events with Kobbe.">
  <h1>Custom events</h1>
  <p>
    Track button clicks, form submissions, and other interactions without
    writing JavaScript.
  </p>

  <h2>HTML attributes</h2>
  <p>
    Add <code>data-kobbe-event</code> to any element. Clicks on that
    element will be tracked as a custom event.
  </p>
  <pre><code>&lt;button
  type="button"
  data-kobbe-event="Newsletter signup"
  data-kobbe-event-source="footer"
&gt;
  Subscribe
&lt;/button&gt;</code></pre>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Attribute</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-kobbe-event</code></td>
        <td>The event name (required).</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><code>data-kobbe-event-*</code></td>
        <td>Optional properties sent as key-value pairs. For example,
        <code>data-kobbe-event-source="footer"</code> sends <code>{`{ source: "footer" }`}</code>.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>JavaScript API</h2>
  <p>
    The tracker sets <code>window.kobbe</code>. Call <code>.track</code>
    from your code after the tracker has loaded.
  </p>
  <pre><code>window.kobbe?.track("Purchase completed", {`{ plan: "pro" }`})</code></pre>
</DocsLayout>
